The 44-year-old was arrested last Thursday following an apparent altercation with police officers at an accident scene. CAPE TOWN A former Springbok rugby player is expected in the Cape Town Magistrates Court on Monday on charges of assault, intimidation and resisting arrest. The 44-year-old was arrested last Thursday following an apparent altercation with police officers at an accident scene.It is understood the suspect, whose name is known to Eyewitness News, was part of the 1995 Rugby World Cup team.